Package: FINEMAPMISS
Type: Package
Title: Fine-mapping meta-analyses with missing information
Version: 1.0
Author: Joonas Kartau and Matti Pirinen
Maintainer: The package maintainer <joonas.kartau@helsinki.fi>
Description: This package contain functions for running FINEMAP-MISS, a Bayesian variable selection method for genetic fine-mapping. This method is an extention of FINEMAP (Benner et al. 2016). FINEMAP-MISS differs from previous methods, as it allows for the combination of multiple datasets across biobanks, while also functioning with missing data. 
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5)
